							<div class="post_wrapper author">
								<div id="about_the_author">
									<div class="gravatar"><a href="https://lithub.com/author/karenteiyamashita/"><img src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/ows_150421669042389-100x100.jpg" width="100" height="100" alt="Karen Tei Yamashita" class="avatar avatar-100 wp-user-avatar wp-user-avatar-100 alignnone photo" /></a></div>
									<div class="description author withsidebar">
										<h6><a href="https://lithub.com/author/karenteiyamashita/">Karen Tei Yamashita</a></h6>
										Karen Tei Yamashita is the author of seven books, including <em>I Hotel</em>, finalist for the National Book Award, and most recently, <em>Letters to Memory</em>, all published by Coffee House Press. Recipient of the John Dos Passos Prize for Literature and a U.S. Artists’ Ford Foundation Fellowship, she is professor emerita of literature and creative writing at the University of California, Santa Cruz.																			</div>
